"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"If you are familiar with automated market maker decentralized exchanges (AMM DEXs) then you have probably heard the terms “liquidity provider” and “impermanent loss”. Liquidity providers experience impermanent loss when the price of deposited tokens changes relative to the time of deposit. A larger deviation incurs more impermanent loss.\\n\\nIt is important to understand why impermanent loss is not permanent. Loss isn’t realized until a liquidity provider withdraws LP tokens. Before becoming a liquidity provider, be sure to completely understand impermanent loss. Doing so will help to significantly mitigate risk.\\n\\n## Automated Market Makers and Liquidity Providers \\n\\nAutomated Market Maker DEXs like the [Loop DEX](http://dex.loop.markets/) use oracles to estimate the current market price of assets, and trade assets into a liquidity pool, as opposed to an order book. Liquidity pools must contain both assets in the pair being traded. For example, the LOOP-UST pool contains deposits of both LOOP and UST. By interacting with an AMM, anyone can become a market maker and earn trading fees and additional incentives.\\n\\n![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/FtNz-yRtVmXB9BpG8rP9u.jpg?height=360&width=638)\\n\\n\",\"timestamp\":1638353255,\"title\":\"A Liquidity Provider Must Understand Impermanent Loss\"},\"digest\":\"inUunDWFDsH_301WWQPJBSBNIpjDkd-1RG3XY03xAQo\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xC6F220eaD0925689cF93F282b18cc3C22B16624b\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"-xmpUjPHanLELC0GkY7eo_7MLxrUj59ifUVCnrcflhA\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"bm4Uz2bCJ_hdIRGeFZ4pLzooNdy8_moozUoMDmhuvYM\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"QUN2e6vn_KSBH73asXOY2iXMkh2b4y5n2KNsfCDOnImIEwq7NflKj3Ls5G9oTp5jIb5MW2qdp9HCnN83MOb2jA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xabd0377ec727fbcaa883413f84eb3ab54ce7a65f198230fc1dd0819249255f001005689e33e6e7bf18eef7425d7804529fc41acb0c2b51ba9c